Boil a full #kettle{}.

When boiling, pour into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat. Add the @Basmati Rice{150%g} and cook for ~{10-12%minutes}.

Drain in a #sieve{} and pop back in the pan. Cover with a #lid{} and leave to the side until ready to serve.

Quarter the @Closed Cup Mushrooms{375%g}.

Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat.

Once hot, add the mushrooms to the pan and season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. Cook until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}, stirring occasionally.

Turn down the heat slightly to medium-high, then add the garlic and @Smoked Paprika{1%tsp} to the pan. Stir-fry until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in the @Water for the Sauce{100%ml} and @Vegetable Stock Paste{1%tbsp}.

Reserve a couple of tablespoons of @Creme Fraiche{75%g} in a #small bowl{}, then stir the remaining creme fraiche into the mushrooms.

Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer until thickened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

In the meantime, roughly chop the @Flat Leaf Parsley{1%bunch}.

Once the sauce has thickened, stir in the @Dijon Mustard{1%tsp} and @Worcester Sauce{2%tsp}.

Add the @Baby Spinach{100%g} to the pan a handful at a time until wilted and piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. > TIP: Add a splash of water if it's a little thick.

Stir in half the parsley, then remove from the heat.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{}, then share between your #serving bowls{}.

Spoon the creamy mushroom stroganoff over the rice.

Top with a spoonful of the reserved creme fraiche, then scatter with the remaining parsley. Enjoy!